.TH "git alias.mergeto(1) User manual" "" "May, 2020" "" ""
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
git mergeto
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
git mergeto branch - stow working copy, merge with first argument, then
unstow
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
git mergeto is a helper alias to merge HEAD onto another branch.
.IP "1." 3
Ensures that the current HEAD is not a detached HEAD
.IP "2." 3
Ensures that the proper number of arguments have been provided
.IP "3." 3
Ensures that the provided argument is associated with a branch
.IP "4." 3
Calls the stow alias to temporarily store the Workspace
.IP "5." 3
Switch to the target branch for merging
.IP "6." 3
Ensures that the new HEAD after the switch is not a detached HEAD
.IP "7." 3
Execute the merge
.IP "8." 3
Calls the unstow alias to restore the Workspace to its former condition
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP \[bu] 2
git mergeto $(git brupstream)
.IP \[bu] 2
git mergeto master
.SH SEE ALSO
.PP
mergefrom finishto rebaseto
.SH DETAILS
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
mergeto = \[dq]!f() { : git man mergeto; \[rs]
    if ! git symbolic-ref HEAD; then echo \[aq]on detached head\[aq]; return 1; fi; \[rs]
    [ $# -ne 1 ] && echo \[aq]Usage: mergeto branch\[aq] && return 1; \[rs]
    PREV=$(git symbolic-ref HEAD | cut -d/ -f3-); \[rs]
    if ! git show-ref $1; then echo \[aq]branch not a named ref\[aq]; return 1; fi; \[rs]
    if ! git stow; then return 1; fi; \[rs]
    git checkout $1; \[rs]
    if ! git symbolic-ref HEAD; then git switch -; git unstow; echo $1 \[aq]would be a detached head\[aq]; return 1; fi; \[rs]
    if ! git merge $PREV; then git mt; git commit; fi; \[rs]
    git unstow; \[rs]
}; f\[dq]
\f[R]
.fi
